  "Message": "feat: Add Flutter SDK with complete architecture matching Swift SDK (#191)\n\n* feat: Add Flutter SDK with complete architecture matching Swift SDK\n\nCreate a new Flutter SDK implementation that mirrors the iOS Swift SDK\narchitecture, providing a privacy-first, on-device AI SDK for Flutter\napplications.\n\n- Main RunAnywhere class with static methods (initialize, chat, generate, transcribe)\n- Event system (EventBus, SDKEvent, SDKGenerationEvent, SDKVoiceEvent, SDKModelEvent)\n- Error handling (SDKError with factory constructors)\n- Configuration models (SDKEnvironment, SDKInitParams, SupabaseConfig)\n- Public models (GenerationResult, GenerationOptions, ModelInfo, PerformanceMetrics)\n\n- Text Generation: GenerationService, StreamingService, ContextManager, ThinkingParser\n- Voice: VoiceCapabilityService, VADHandler, VoiceService protocol\n- Model Loading: ModelLoadingService, ValidationService, DownloadService\n- Memory: MemoryService with pressure detection\n- Analytics: GenerationAnalyticsService for performance tracking\n\n- Components: BaseComponent, Component protocol, ComponentState enum\n- Protocols: LLMService, MemoryManager, ModelStorageManager, ModelLifecycleProtocol, HardwareDetector\n- Models: ModelCategory, RequestPriority, DeviceCapabilities, FrameworkModality, LLMFramework\n- Service Registry: UnifiedServiceRegistry for adapter management\n\n- Repositories: Repository protocol, ConfigurationRepository with SQLite implementation\n- Storage: DatabaseManager (SQLite), FileStorageManager for model files\n- Network: APIClient protocol, APIClientImpl using Dio\n- Entities: ConfigurationEntity for persistence\n\n- Dependency Injection: ServiceContainer with lazy initialization\n- Logging: SDKLogger with category support\n- Event System: EventBus for decoupled communication\n\n- ✅ SDK initialization with environment support (development/staging/production)\n- ✅ Text generation with streaming support\n- ✅ Voice transcription support\n- ✅ Model management (load, list, download)\n- ✅ Event-driven architecture\n- ✅ Service container for dependency injection\n- ✅ Database storage with SQLite\n- ✅ File system storage for models\n- ✅ Network client with Dio\n- ✅ Memory management with pressure detection\n- ✅ Analytics tracking\n\n- dio: HTTP client\n- sqflite: SQLite database\n- path_provider: File system access\n- device_info_plus: Device information\n- flutter_secure_storage: Secure storage\n- logger: Logging\n- get_it: Dependency injection\n- rxdart: Reactive streams\n- crypto: Cryptography\n- archive: Archive handling\n\nlib/\n├── public/ # Public API layer\n├── capabilities/ # Feature-specific business logic\n├── core/ # Domain models and protocols\n├── data/ # Data persistence and network\n├── foundation/ # Cross-cutting utilities\n└── components/ # Component implementations\n\n- All compilation errors fixed\n- Architecture matches Swift SDK structure\n- Ready for implementation of actual ML framework integrations\n- Only info-level warnings (style suggestions)\n\nThis SDK provides the same clean architecture and developer experience as\nthe Swift SDK, enabling cross-platform AI application development.\n\n* Updated SDK and Added Example app",
